    "YFP-Polη was redistributed to nuclear repair foci following TMZ-treatment in RAD18 +/+ but not RAD18 -/-U373 cells (Fig. 4e).",
    "Surprisingly, POLH knockdown using siRNA led to decreased TMZ sensitivity in both RAD18 +/+ and RAD18 -/-U373 cells.",
    "However, POLH siRNA did not affect TMZ sensitivity in POLK -/-cells (Fig. 4f).",
    "To elucidate the relationship between Polκ and Polη in the TMZ response, we quantified GFP-Polκ foci in POLH-depleted cells.",
    "As shown in Fig. 4g, POLH knockdown led to an increased percentage of cells with PCNAcolocalizing GFP-Polκ foci."
